{"word":"στάχυς","slug":"στάχυς","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>στάχυς</b></el> <p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>an ear of corn</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>spica</el>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a>, <el>στ. ἄτης</el> <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; of the Theban <el>Σπαρτοί</el>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>generally, <i>a scion, child, progeny</i>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}